---
import PagePlate from "@/layouts/PagePlate.astro";
---

<PagePlate title="Cookies Policy">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-6 sm:px-8 text-gray-800 leading-relaxed">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Cookies Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mb-12">Last updated: November 2025</p>

    <article class="space-y-8">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          This Cookies Policy explains how <strong>Tara G!</strong> uses cookies and similar technologies
          to enhance your experience on our website. By continuing to use our site, you agree to the use of
          cookies as described in this policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">2. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help websites
          remember your preferences, improve usability, and analyze how visitors interact with the platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">3. How We Use Cookies</h2>
        <p>We use cookies for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Essential Cookies</strong> – Necessary for the website to function (e.g., login sessions and security features).</li>
          <li><strong>Performance Cookies</strong> – Help us understand how users interact with Tara G! to improve user experience.</li>
          <li><strong>Preference Cookies</strong> – Remember user choices such as region, trip filters, or display preferences.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics Cookies</strong> – Provide anonymous insights into how users find and use the site.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">4. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Some features of Tara G! may rely on third-party services, such as Mapbox or analytics tools.
          These services may place their own cookies to track usage or improve functionality.
          Tara G! does not control these cookies and recommends reviewing each provider’s own cookie policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">5. Managing Your Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          You can control or delete cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>Block cookies from specific sites or all sites.</li>
          <li>Delete existing cookies stored on your device.</li>
          <li>Set notifications when a website attempts to store cookies.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality or performance of
          <strong>Tara G!</strong>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">6. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookies Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements.
          Any updates will be posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">7. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          For any questions or concerns about our use of cookies, you can reach us at:<br />
          <strong>Email:</strong> support@tarag.ph
        </p>
      </section>

    </article>
  </section>
</PagePlate>
